<section xml:id="C15.S15">
<title>Sums</title>          
<para xml:id="C15.S15.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="15.15.1" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S15.E1">\mathbf{F}\left({a,b\atop c};\frac{1}{z}\right)=\left(1-\frac{z_{0}}{z}\right) ^{-a}\sum_{s=0}^{\infty}\frac{(a)_{s}}{s!}\*\mathbf{F}\left({-s,b\atop c}; \frac{1}{z_{0}}\right)\left(1-\frac{z}{z_{0}}\right)^{-s}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.s2">
Here <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.m1">z_{0}</Math> ( <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.m2">{\neq 0}</Math> ) is an arbitrary complex constant and the expansion converges when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.m3">|z-z_{0}|&gt;\max(|z_{0}|,|z_{0}-1|)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C15.S15.p1.s3">
For further information seeBühring (1987a) and Kalla (1992).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C15.S15.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C15.S15.p2.s1">
For compendia of finite sums and infinite series involving hypergeometric functions see Prudnikov et al. (1990, §§5.3 and 6.7) andHansen (1975).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</section>
